            "answer_text": "Folk medicine. Poultices of things like sweet gum, Myrtle and yellodock that helped close open wounds. Willow bark tea (natural aspirin) for pain relief. Spanish moss for swelling and pain - and Spanish moss was fairly common in many southern areas. Some bits of folk medicine was nothing but superstition but herb craft had real benefits. And though they didn\u2019t know why, they used natural antibiotics and anti-microbial like honey and garlic, rosemary, sage, basil, oregano, thyme, cardamom, and clove. ",
